e for both dogs and...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Charlottesville\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":9,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/atlantic-coast-k-9-training-service\",\"name\":\"Atlantic Coast K-9 Training Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/atlantic-coast-k-9-training-service\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about Atlantic Coast K-9 Training Service.  What makes this dog facility special is its friendly, caring, convenient. The staff's dedication to creating a positive...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Charlottesville\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":10,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/crate-marrow\",\"name\":\"Crate & Marrow\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/crate-marrow\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about Crate & Marrow.  What makes this dog facility special is its great, convenient, professional. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience for both dogs...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Charlottesville\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}25:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2d\"}}]\n2e:T5da,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are there off-leash swimming spots in Charlottesville?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes—Chris Greene Lake Park features a dedicated one-acre fenced off-leash area that includes a \\\"dog beach,\\\" allowing pups to swim safely in the lake. It is one of the premier aquatic socialization spots in the region.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"When can dogs be off-leash on the Rivanna Trail?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Charlottesville has a unique schedule for the Rivanna Trail at Riverview Park, allowing dogs to be off-leash specifically on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays. On all other days, strict leash laws apply to ensure trail safety.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Does Charlottesville offer a lifetime dog license?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes—the City of Charlottesville offers a unique lifetime dog license for a one-time fee of $10, provided you maintain current rabies vaccinations. This is a highly cost-effective alternative to annual renewals found in other Virginia counties.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is the Saunders-Monticello Trail dog-friendly?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Saunders-Monticello Trail is extremely dog-friendly for leashed pets, offering an ADA-compliant 2-mile path with stunning views. However, dogs must remain on a leash at all times to protect the historical landscape and wildlife.\"}}]}26:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2e\"}}]\n27:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Charlottesville\\\"}]}\"}}]\n28:[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n29:[\"$\",\"$L2f\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n2a:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Charlottesville\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"City spotlight\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks in Charlottesville, VA\"}],\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Discover the best mountain runs and dog-friendly swimming spots in the Blue Ridge foothills, from Chris Greene Lake to the historic Saunders-Monticello Trail.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Charlottesville, Virginia, offers a unique blend of historical charm and adventurous outdoor opportunities for dog owners nestled in the foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains. The city is renowned for its progressive approach to pet amenities, highlighted by the \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.albemarle.org/government/parks-recreation/parks/chris-greene-lake-park\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Chris Greene Lake Park\"}],null,\", which features a dedicated one-acre fenced \\\"dog beach\\\" where pups can swim freely in the lake. For trail enthusiasts, the \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.rivannatrail.org/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Rivanna Trail\"}],null,\" provides a scenic escape, famously offering a flexible off-leash policy at Riverview Park on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays—a rare schedule that caters to local socialization needs. Urban explorers often flock to \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"7\",{\"href\":\"https://www.charlottesville.gov/Facilities/Facility/Details/Azalea-Park-1\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Azalea Park\"}],null,\", home to one of the city's most established fenced enclosures with separate areas for different breed sizes, ensuring a safe and engaging environment for the entire community.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Beyond the parks, Charlottesville’s dog culture extends into its world-class beverage scene and historical landmarks. The \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.monticello.org/visit/the-saunders-monticello-trail/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Saunders-Monticello Trail\"}],null,\" offers a stunning, ADA-compliant two-mile path up to Thomas Jefferson’s estate; while a strict leash law is enforced here to protect the sensitive landscape, it remains a premier destination for leashed forest hikes. Local favorites like King Family Vineyards even welcome four-legged fans to their weekly polo matches, creating a sophisticated social atmosphere for pets. Navigating the city’s requirements is made easy with a unique lifetime dog license available for a one-time $10 fee, provided rabies vaccinations remain current. For those looking to invest in this thriving pet market, our \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/owner-resources\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"owner resources\"}],null,\" offer critical data on development and zoning. From the \\\"Paws and Pints\\\" culture at local breweries to the quiet beauty of the Blue Ridge, Charlottesville remains an elite destination for Virginia’s active canine companions.\"]}]]}],\"$L31\",\"$L32\"]}],\"$L33\"]}]}],\"$L34\",\"$L35\",\"$L36\",\"$L37\",\"$L38\",\"$L39\",\"$L3a\",\"$L3b\",\"$L3c\",\"$L3d\",\"$L3e\",\"$L3f\"]}]\n2b:[\"$\",\"footer\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-new\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-container\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-grid\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-column\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h4\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-heading\",\"children\":\"IndoorDogPark\"}],[\"$\",\"ul\",null,{\"className\":\"footer-links\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",null,{\"chil